You are granted a worldwide, royalty-free, non-exclusive, non-transferable copyright license (without the right to sublicense) to use, copy, modify, and redistribute the Software strictly for the following purposes (Note: Patent rights are governed separately under Section 5):

Academic & Scientific Research: Publishing papers, running experiments, and open benchmarking of quantum hardware.

Internal Corporate Evaluation: Engineers and researchers at commercial entities may use the Software internally to evaluate its performance. This explicitly includes the right to execute the Software on third-party cloud hardware (e.g., IBM Quantum, AWS Braket) strictly for internal R&D, and the right to redistribute the Software internally within the same legal entity.

3. COMMERCIAL USE RESTRICTIONS
To sustainably fund the ongoing R&D of this architecture, commercial deployment requires a separate commercial license. You may not use this Software or its derivatives (including but not limited to API wrappers, integrated workflows, and modified binaries) for:

Cloud & Platform Integration: Integrating the Software into commercial Quantum-as-a-Service (QaaS) platforms, cloud APIs, or proprietary hardware control stacks offered to third parties.

Commercial Software Products: Bundling the Software into paid enterprise error-suppression, quantum middleware products, or proprietary benchmarking services.

